The paper discusses the use of automated methods to improve the quality of opening books in chess engines, which involves machine learning and decision-making algorithms, suggesting a strong association between humans' and machines' choices of opening moves. This makes cs.AI the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves statistical analysis, which is relevant to cs.LG and cs.CV. The use of game theory and decision-making algorithms is relevant to cs.GT, while the use of databases and algorithms to compile opening books is relevant to cs.PL.
